<title>Malnutrition deaths</title>
<content type="html" xml:lang="en">&lt;p&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/feb/05/figures-show-rise-in-malnutrition-deaths-in-england-and-wales&#34;&gt; Deaths due to malnutrition are increasing in England, &lt;/a&gt; as welfare often provides too little money for poor people to pay for housing, medical care and food, for themselves or for their children. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Many US college students skip food because they are broke. &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2018/02/04/even-elite-colleges-students-going-hungry/GMDfGe89ocg31Fm1cmzR2J/story.html?s_campaign=8315&#34;&gt; At MIT, 10% of the students each week skipped a meal due to lack of funds. &lt;/a&gt;   This is not yet malnutrition, but it can retard their studies, and it would never happen if the educational system worked.   &lt;/p&gt;</content>
<category term="stallman"/>
